Text: What have been the goals for the week and what did I achieve?
To choose a project - Achieved
To join a group - Achieved
Understand the project- Achieved
Start the proposal - Partly achieved
What (parts of the workflow/research/development) was working well and why?
I did some good research on the company and aspects of the project so I think I had a decent understanding heading into the meeting with the client.
During the meeting with the client, I felt I asked some good questions to further mine and my teams understanding of the project.
After the meeting with the client, I believe I have increased my understanding of the project and now feel I have a good idea of where we are headed.
What (parts of the workflow/research/development) was not working well and why?
It was a struggle getting the groups sorted out with one person being quite adamant on a particular project.
Luckily other people moved projects to accommodate them.
I haven't contributed to the proposal as much as I would like to have done.
I put this down to having to finish off another assignment.
What would I do differently if I would be faced with the same situation or goals?
I could maybe improve my time management skills.
Or I could not over-commit myself knowing what I have on my plate and not make my or my teams' expectations as high.
What did I learn this week and/or what am I proud of or satisfied with?
I now have a better understanding of some tech concepts such as API's, Web Responsive Apps, Active Directory.
Sometimes group work definitely needs a leader or someone to take charge especially if there is little to no structure or you will struggle to achieve anything
I am happy I have a good understanding of the project (or at least I hope I do).
Overall
